cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CE, cs.DS, cs.IT

This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new method for dynamic experiments using thompson sampling. It also involves simulation studies to evaluate the performance of the proposed method. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as thompson sampling is a popular method in reinforcement learning and decision-making problems. 

The paper may also fall under cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) as it discusses the use of the proposed method in a real service environment. 

cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possible category as the paper involves the use of statistical models and algorithms for dynamic experiments. 

Finally, cs.IT (Information Theory) could be a relevant category as the paper discusses the reparameterization of a logistic model with odds ratio parameters, which is a concept from information theory.
